Use a slightly different color accent from the wormhole button to distinguish constellation links visually. A warm gold/purple tint works well:

```css
.constellationBtn {
    display: inline-block;
    padding: 8px 22px;
    background: rgba(176, 95, 255, 0.12);
    border: 1px solid rgba(176, 95, 255, 0.35);
    border-radius: 10px;
    color: #b05fff;
    font-size: 12px;
    font-weight: 600;
    font-family: inherit;
    cursor: pointer;
    transition: background 0.2s, border-color 0.2s;
    white-space: nowrap;
    overflow: hidden;
    text-overflow: ellipsis;
    max-width: 100%;
}

.constellationBtn:hover {
    background: rgba(176, 95, 255, 0.22);
    border-color: rgba(176, 95, 255, 0.55);
}
```

The purple (`#b05fff`) is from `STAR_COLORS[4]` and visually distinguishes constellation links from wormhole links (blue `#5f92ff`).

---

### Answers to Design Questions

**Q1: Constellation indicator -- ring stroke vs modify shadowColor?**

Ring stroke. An additional `Circle` with `stroke` and no `fill`, positioned at `r * 2.8` radius. Modifying the existing `shadowColor` would change the star's fundamental color identity (which is tied to the author's userId). A separate ring layer communicates "this star has connections" without altering what the star _is_. The ring is also `listening={false}` so it has zero interaction cost.

**Q2: Constellation glow lines -- Konva Line with shadowBlur vs Canvas2D Shape?**

Canvas2D `Shape` with `sceneFunc`. While Konva `Line` does support `shadowBlur`, it creates one shadow per node, and with the multi-layer approach we need, that would mean 3 Konva Line nodes per constellation link (already the case, and it results in many nodes). A single `Shape` batches all line drawing into one canvas pass, uses Canvas2D's native `shadowBlur` (which composites correctly with the strokes), and matches the proven pattern in `WormholeLayer.jsx` and the semantic bridges `Shape` in `InteractiveLayer.jsx`. The `Text` labels remain as Konva `Text` nodes because they need `scaleX/scaleY` zoom correction which is cumbersome in raw Canvas2D.

**Q3: Star titles -- SQL RPC vs posts Map?**

SQL RPC. The `find_wormhole_pairs` RPC already includes `a_title, b_title` by selecting from the same `journals` table it JOINs. The `get_viewport_constellations` RPC already JOINs `journals ja` and `journals jb` -- adding `ja.title AS a_title, jb.title AS b_title` costs zero additional query overhead. The posts Map is unreliable for this purpose because constellation links can span vast universe distances, and the linked star may never have been fetched in the current viewport session.

---

### Implementation Sequence

1. **SQL RPC update** -- Add `a_title, b_title` to `get_viewport_constellations`. Deploy this first since it is backward-compatible (the new columns simply did not exist before, so existing code ignores them).

2. **Feature 1 (Star indicators)** -- `constellationUtils.js` is unchanged. Add the `constellationStarColors` memo in `Universe.jsx`, thread it through `InteractiveLayer.jsx`, and add the ring `Circle` in `StarGroup.jsx`. This is self-contained and testable independently.

3. **Feature 2 (Glow lines)** -- Rewrite `ConstellationLayer.jsx` to use the Canvas2D `Shape` approach. This can be tested independently since it does not change any props or data structures.

4. **Feature 3 (Travel buttons)** -- Add `getConstellationLinksForPost` and `handleConstellationTravel` to `Universe.jsx`, add JSX buttons to the preview panel, and add `.constellationBtn` CSS class. Depends on Step 1 (SQL) being deployed for titles to appear.

Features 1 and 2 have no dependencies on each other and can be implemented in parallel. Feature 3 depends on the SQL change from Step 1.

---

### Critical Files for Implementation

- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\Universe\layers\ConstellationLayer.jsx` - Full rewrite from Konva Lines to Canvas2D Shape for ethereal glow rendering (Feature 2)
- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\Universe\Universe.jsx` - Add constellationStarColors memo, getConstellationLinksForPost, handleConstellationTravel, and preview panel buttons (Features 1 and 3)
- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\Universe\components\StarGroup.jsx` - Add constellationColor prop and ring Circle indicator (Feature 1)
- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\client\src\components\Universe\layers\InteractiveLayer.jsx` - Thread constellationStarColors prop through to StarGroup (Feature 1)
- `C:\Users\johnm\iskrib_v3\server\sql\constellations.sql` - Add a_title, b_title columns to get_viewport_constellations RPC return type (Feature 3)

